At least five people are dying every day in the  northern Angolan town of Ndalatando for want of food and medical attention,  official radio reported Sunday.
It said some 5,000 townspeople had returned to Ndalatando sionce the army  recaptured it from rebel forces on May 4.
At least 15,000 people in Ndalatando's Kwanza-norte province are suffering  from severe malnutrition, the radio said.
